# Shell scripts and the git hook must stay LF so they run under bash on Linux CI
# and git-bash on Windows. With core.autocrlf=true a CRLF working copy injects a
# stray $'\r' that breaks the shebang and command lines. Scope is intentionally
# narrow (no tree-wide `text=auto`) to avoid renormalization churn.
*.sh text eol=lf
.githooks/pre-push text eol=lf
